    "description": {
      "en": {
        "provenance": "imported",
        "value": "Gender responsive macroeconomic and sectoral policies - Provide technical support, including capacity development, policy advisory support and facilitation of policy dialogues, to the national and local governments [MoWCSW, MoLE, MoFALD] to effectively integrate, implement and monitor gender equality provisions in macro-economic and sectoral policies in alignment with international and national commitments on gender equality and women’s empowerment, including localization of GRB, safe labour migration and GESI-responsive policiesEconomic competency of excluded women's groups - Provide excluded women including out-of-school adolescent girls and young women in UN Women's programme districts, with a) vocational skills and entrepreneurship development training, b) business development/start-up support including technical, material and counseling support, c) facilitation of business and market linkages, and d) awareness/sensitization training on GESI including access to information on women's entitlements and EVAW services.  Economic leadership of excluded women's groups - Continue supporting capacity enhancement (leadership and result-based management) with excluded women's groups to influence local decision-making processes for  mainstreaming of gender equality provisions and mobilization of locally available resources for women's empowerment and to increase excluded women's participation in local bodies"
      },
      "ne": null
    },
